06/08/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Officials from the defence ministry and the foreign and EU integration ministry met in Zagreb on Sunday (August 5th) to discuss how to expand campaigns on the benefits of EU and NATO membership.
The two ministries have put information stands on the issue around the capital and plan stands in other parts of the country as well.
Meanwhile two separate polls, published in Vecernji List newspaper at the weekend, suggest the campaigns may be working.
A poll by Promocija plus agency finds support for NATO and EU accession was at 53.8% in July, up by 2.2% compared to June.
The second poll by Metron/Vectura put public support of EU accession at 53.7% in July.
(Vecernji List - 06/08/07;
HINA, HRT - 05/08/07)
